title: Baby Catcher: Chronicles of a Modern Midwife
description: A former nurse chronicles her journey into midwifery, from her dissatisfaction with formulaic delivery room procedures in the 1960s to her eventual career as a "baby catcher," and chronicles her diverse birth experiences, the women she has encountered along the way, and role of midwifery in the United States. 35,000 first printing.
author: Peggy Vincent
